{{Source Notation|date=January 2013}}
'''Yoshida Shichifukujin''' (吉田七福神) is a pilgrimage {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神}} {{ill|pilgrimage site|ja|札所}} located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}} {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}. It was established in Heisei 9 ({{ill|1997|ja|1997年}}). It is composed of eight temples, including the {{ill|Daruma Daishi|ja|達磨大師}}’s Toyohashi-kaku {{ill|Nisshin-in|ja|日進院}}.

== Overview ==
* Area: Entirely within {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}
* Operating Period: Year-round

== List of Yoshida Shichifukujin ==
* {{ill|Jingūji (Toyohashi)|ja|神宮寺 (豊橋市)}} (located in Uomachi, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵比須}}
* {{ill|Fumonji (Toyohashi)|ja|普門寺 (豊橋市)}} (located in Nabeyamashita, Unya-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Daikokuten|ja|大黒天}}
* {{ill|Hōgyōin|ja|宝形院}} (located in Minamichūhata, Mukayama-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Fukurokuju|ja|福禄寿}}
* {{ill|Akaiwa-ji|ja|赤岩寺}} (located in Aka-iwayama, Tome-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Benzaiten|ja|弁才天}}
* {{ill|Eifuku-ji (Toyohashi-Shimojicho)|ja|永福寺 (豊橋市下地町)}} (located in Kitamura, Shimojicho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Bishamonten|ja|毘沙門天}}
* {{ill|Jōshin-ji|ja|常心寺}} (located in Amatsuhashi, Sugiyama-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Hotei|ja|布袋}}
* {{ill|Yakushi-ji (Toyohashi)|ja|薬師寺 (豊橋市)}} (located in Ushikawa Yakushi-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Jurojin|ja|寿老人}}
* {{ill|Toyohashi-kaku Nisshin Zen-ji|ja|豊橋閣日進禅寺}} (located in Shinyoshi-cho, {{ill|Toyohashi City|ja|豊橋市}}) – {{ill|Daruma Daishi|ja|達磨}} Daisi

== Related Articles ==
* {{ill|Mikawa Seven Lucky Gods|ja|三河七福神}}
* {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神}}

== External Links ==
*[http://www.gld.mmtr.or.jp/~yuchan/etc/yoshida7fuku.html 参考サイト]{{Broken Link|date=November 2016}}

